def max_xor_xnor(a, b, n):

    def xnor(a, b):
        if a < b:
            (a, b) = (b, a)
        if a == 0 and b == 0:
            return 1
        a_rem = 0
        b_rem = 0
        count = 0
        xnornum = 0
        while a != 0:
            a_rem = a & 1
            b_rem = b & 1
            if a_rem == b_rem:
                xnornum |= 1 << count
            count += 1
            a = a >> 1
            b = b >> 1
        return xnornum
    c = a | b
    d = xnor(a, b)
    p = [a, b, c]
    r = [a, b, d]
    k = n % 3 - 1
    return max(p[k], r[k])
